# ~/claude-discord/<instance>/.bot.env — per-instance overrides for the
# claude-discord@.service systemd unit. install.sh <instance> seeds this
# file from this template; edit it before starting the bot.
#
# Systemd reads the file as plain KEY=VALUE pairs. No shell expansion,
# no quoting tricks — write literal paths.

# --- REQUIRED -----------------------------------------------------------

# The `claude --resume <name>` session this bot should resume. Must
# already exist (use `claude -n <name>` to create it first).
BOT_SESSION_NAME=changeme

# --- OPTIONAL -----------------------------------------------------------

# Space-separated plugin specs for --dangerously-load-development-channels.
# Omit if you only use marketplace-installed plugins.
# BOT_PLUGINS=plugin:discord@vox-plugins plugin:scheduler@vox-plugins

# Screen session name the wrapper runs `claude` inside. Defaults to
# `claude-discord-<instance>` (set by the unit from %i), which is already
# unique per instance. Only override if you have a reason.
# SCREEN_SESSION=my-custom-screen

# Personality / add-dir. Defaults to `~/claude-discord/<instance>/claude-personality`
# (set by the unit from %i). Override if your personality lives elsewhere.
# BOT_ADD_DIR=/home/you/some/other/dir

# --- MODEL SELECTION (optional) ----------------------------------------

# Override the default model / subagent model / effort level. Omit to
# use Claude Code's defaults.
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-7
# CLAUDE_CODE_SUBAGENT_MODEL=claude-opus-4-7
# CLAUDE_CODE_EFFORT_LEVEL=max
# CLAUDE_CODE_AUTO_COMPACT_WINDOW=750000
